The paper deals with image denoising using neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of simulated noisy images also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT).
